review_blob: When visiting Wisconsin I tried this brew and could not get enough of it. I brought several cases of it home with me back to Arkansas. Its simply a really rich and flavorful beer that is not too heavy. It goes down perfectly while hot-tubbing in the snow. My only complaint is that you cant buy it outside of Wisconsin.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: This is one of my all-time favorite brews. It is light and refreshing and full of flavor. My fridge is never without a six pack of this beer. My girlfriend doesnt like beer much (why I keep her around I dont know...ha!) but she LOVES this beer. Its the only beer she enjoys drinking. It has a subtle fruitiness to it that is very well balanced...in other words, it is not a fruit flavored beer per se, it simply has some soft fruity highlights.
This is a wonderfully hoppy brew. It has a crisp clean flavor with an abundance of aromatic hops while keeping the bittering hops to a bare minimum. Very tasty!
beer_name: Odell St. Lupulin Extra Pale Ale
